{
  "stem": "13251.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It has a cathedral that's-- that's supposed to be the-- it's not the largest.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It's the tallest cathedral in England, I think.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It's built hundreds of years ago.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I-- it's so fascinating to see how hundreds of years ago, they're-- they're able to build something with such accuracy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, I mean, it's like symmetric, and perfect, and huge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't have any equipment in those days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyway, it still stands there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And opposite the cathedral is this house that Oliver Cromwell lived in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was a Puritan that-- that took power from King Charles, I believe-- you know, if you know anything about English history.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and when he took over, because of his religious beliefs, he smashed all the-- the beautiful pane-- windows-- glass-- in the cathedral, which has been replaced since.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, his house, we-- we were invited for tea there as-- as kids, several times, by the vicar.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's a-- his house is-- is the permanent residence of the Vicar of Ely, which is like, the-- he's the highest--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--Christian, whatever, you know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he had these nice church boys over to--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, he invited us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, it wasn't him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His wife, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Knowles-- very, very lovely lady-- she would invite us for tea there, and a couple of times, yeah, we went there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Well, we--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--visited a good-- no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This wasn't-- this was outside the-- the, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oliver Cromwell's house was a residence of the vicar, that was opposite-- across from the-- from-- there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was like a-- a-- a big grass lawn-- a huge area-- I don't know, a few acres.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And beyond that was-- outside like, the gate was-- was the building for-- the residence.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jewish Free School was totally non-religious.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
